    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Restraining structures incorporating a barrier that is raised or pushed aside at the start of a race, to ensure a simultaneous start for all competitors or to ensure consistent timing of each competitor. Examples are used in horse racing, foot races, downhill skiing, and other sports.</Note_Text>
